  "prompt": "Which are the companies that hire freshers in Analytics (R programming)?",
  "response": "There are several companies known to hire freshers with skills in analytics and R programming. These companies span various industries such as technology, finance, consulting, healthcare, and more. Some of the notable companies include:\n\n1. **Tech Companies**:\n   - Google\n   - Facebook (Meta)\n   - Microsoft\n   - Amazon\n   - IBM\n   - Oracle\n\n2. **Consulting Firms**:\n   - Deloitte\n   - Accenture\n   - EY (Ernst & Young)\n   - PwC (PricewaterhouseCoopers)\n   - KPMG\n   - McKinsey & Company\n   - Boston Consulting Group (BCG)\n\n3. **Financial Institutions**:\n   - JPMorgan Chase\n   - Goldman Sachs\n   - Morgan Stanley\n   - American Express\n   - Bank of America\n\n4. **Healthcare and Biotech**:\n   - McKesson\n   - Cerner Corporation\n   - IQVIA\n   - Roche\n\n5. **Retail and Consumer Goods**:\n   - Walmart\n   - Target\n   - Unilever\n   - Procter & Gamble\n\n6. **Telecommunications**:\n   - AT&T\n   - Verizon\n   - Vodafone\n\n7. **Startups and Smaller Firms**:\n   - Numerous startups and smaller companies in the tech and data analytics space are often eager to hire fresh talent to bring innovative ideas and fresh perspectives.\n\nWhen looking for roles, freshers should search for job titles such as Data Analyst, Business Analyst, Data Scientist (entry-level), or Junior Data Analyst. It's also helpful to regularly check job portals, company career pages, and LinkedIn for openings specifically targeting freshers. Networking through platforms like LinkedIn and attending industry events or workshops can also provide valuable opportunities to connect with potential employers.",
